OL,5,Cstabbing
OL,7,FThe court heard the defendant's father
OL,8,Fhad failed to wake up on time on the
OL,9,Fmorning of the 24 April before his
OL,10,Fdaughter left for school.
OL,12,FThe 14-year-old defendant, who cannot
OL,13,Fbe identified, has pleaded guilty to
OL,14,Fthree counts of wounding with intent
OL,15,Fand one of possession of a bladed
OL,16,Farticle on school premises.
OL,18,FThe girl denies three counts of
OL,19,Fattempted murder in relation to the
OL,20,Fincident on April 24 this year, when
OL,21,Fshe was 13.
