OL,7,FThe pupil's father confirmed the knife
OL,8,Fbelonged to him, saying it was a multi-
OL,9,Ftool he had owned for several years,
OL,10,Fwhich he kept with fishing equipment
OL,11,Fin his house.
OL,13,FOn the day of the attack, the
OL,14,Fdefendant's father said he had been
OL,15,Fdecorating and the knife had been left
OL,16,Fon a paint pot in his dining room.
